[2]
Date: 29 Aug 2006
From: Joe Dudley <jdudley@eaicorp.com>
Source: India News
<http://indiaenews.com/2006-08/20331-hantavirus-surat-report.htm>

No hantavirus in Surat: report
------------------------------
Ahmedabad, Aug 29 (IANS): The National Institute of Virology in Pune
declared on Tuesday that there is no hantavirus in the flood ravaged city
of Surat, 250 km from here in south Gujarat. Additional director of NIV, M
S Chaddha said: "NIV collected 46 blood samples from Surat city, and not
even a single sample contained hantavirus."
The medical authorities in Surat, including NIV, have not yet clarified why
2 people (aged 24 and 36) had died last week. The deaths were feared to
have been caused by hantavirus pulmonary syndrome.
Meanwhile, 17 others have lost their lives due to leptospirosis during the
past 15 days, after the floodwater receded. Sixty-six cases of
leptospirosis have been reported in government hospitals hitherto in Surat.
